          '@type': 'Answer',
          text: 'Most love calculators work by taking two names as input and running them through a deterministic algorithm. Common methods include counting letter occurrences, converting characters to numerical values, and applying mathematical operations to generate a percentage score. The result is always the same for the same pair of names, which makes it feel meaningful even though it is based on letters rather than any real compatibility metric.',
