          text: 'Research in relationship psychology identifies several key factors that predict compatibility: shared core values and life goals, effective communication skills, emotional intelligence and empathy, compatible conflict resolution styles, similar levels of commitment, physical and emotional intimacy, and mutual respect. Dr. John Gottman\'s research has found that the ratio of positive to negative interactions during conflict is one of the strongest predictors of relationship success, with successful couples maintaining at least a 5:1 ratio.',
